title: congreso progressive coalitions

You should not be here? Report a bug if you see this text.

@progressive
title: <span style="color: var(--psoe); font-style: italic;">Progressist</span> <span style="color: var(--up);">Coalition</span> (PSOE - [+ congreso_left_carrier +])
subtitle: A difficult arithmetic made possible by kingmaker smaller parties. [? if congreso_coalition_progressive_talks: Pulling it over the line will demand hard concessions. ?]
view-if: congreso_coalition_progressive_s > congreso_s_majority - 50
choose-if: congreso_coalition_progressive_reach and not congreso_coalition_psoe_cs_wtf
unavailable-subtitle: [? if not congreso_coalition_progressive_reach : The numbers don't add up, not even with every abstention that can be realistically negotiated. ?][? if congreso_coalition_psoe_cs_wtf: This does not seem to be the plan of [+ psoe_leader +] and [+ csspa_leader +] ?]
on-arrival: {!
    // TODO — form the PSOE + left-carrier coalition cabinet.
    //   left carrier = Q.congreso_left_carrier (sumar→up→podemos→iu)
    //   • president = psoe, UNLESS Q (sorpasso): leftPodemosLed ⇒ carrier leads.
    //   • the player negotiates support/abstention for concessions — reuse the
    //     *_concessions_indy / *_concessions_social machinery (cf. parlament coalitions).
    //   • Q.congreso_coalition_progressive_talks flags whether the maths needed
    //     escalated (starred) support → bigger asks / lower trust payoff.
    //   • set the "government formed" flags the engine/post_event read.
!}

